title: For Sale:  VEPR 12
postcontent:
VEPR 12 with hand polished Bolt Carrier Group (BCG), hand polished BCG interior Guide Rails, and hand profiled and polished Hammer. This polishing work was professionally done with a selection of hand files and the correct sequence of sanding/polishing grit sand paper and sponge type sand papers to a very fine polish, NOT USING A DREMEL TOOL! Don't try this at home folks ... or follow some of the youtube videos that suggest using dremels!! If you try that and don't get everything exactly right you could end up with a non-functional firearm, a long wait and expense for the right parts, and more expense (around $250 or more) to have a professional do the job correctly, if you can find one!. 
For those of you unfamiliar with the VEPR 12 most of them DO NOT run all kinds of 12 Ga. ammo right out of the box. You must have the BCG, BCG Guide rails, and Hammer polished and correctly profiled. You can find V12’s for less money on Gunbroker or even Armslist etc. but they won’t have the needed work done, or done Correctly ... Plus you need to factor the additional work and parts that this one has had completed. Yes you might save some money but what is that worth if you need the V12 in a self defense situation and it fails to run? Yes, you can buy less for less, or less for more ... but you can't buy more for less.
Now this VEPR 12 runs any type of ammo, or combination of ammo, as fast as you can pull the trigger. It comes with a four position cheek weld and I also added two HK type custom cut and fitted rails on the Russian forearm, a five position folding and contoured forward handle, and a nice custom beavertail to the Russian Handle. This firearm is all Russian. Comes as shown with only 10 rounds through it, fired for full function. Priced below market, in consideration of the extra work, the fact that these are not illegal but just banned with recent sanctions, and the fact that my original retail cost just before the election and pre-polishing etc. was $1799 plus tax, FFL, and shipping.Buyer or seller pays BC for buyer, TBD. This was listed with Saiga as maker since AL doesn't have Molot as an option when listing. I have previously owned top of the line Saiga's for three gun competition etc. but the VEPR 12 is much, much better all round. I'm open to considering partial trades including certain firearms, cash/gold/silver/ and/or CCW. I have listed the V12 for the next week (10/2/17-10/10/17) at $1150 cash only, reduced from $1545 for a quick sale. If I don't sell it this week I will either withdraw the listing or raise it back up to its true value.*Update 10.4.17. Reports show less than 80 New VEPR 12 Shotguns remain available in the US through the exclusive US dealer. After they are gone there are no more available, and none available in the foreseeable future without a change in US politics. Owners Manual and extra factory issued firing pin included in the package. You Can Call Me at seven two zero, 301.5583.

title: For Sale:  TAURUS PT 709 Slim 9mm
postcontent:
TAURUS PT 709 Slim 9mm Has 1 x 7 Round MagazinePerfect for concealed carry, only shot about 50 rounds through this firearm.  Cash only & no shipping.Barrel Length: 3.2Length: 6.2Height: 5.35
The Taurus PT 709 Slim is a semi-automatic small-frame pistol chambered for 9mm. The 709 Slim is part of the Slim series and has is very similar to the 740 Slim  Named “Slim” because it is 1.04″ wide—that’s about 0.1″ to 0.2″ smaller than most other small-frame pistols.
Features include three safeties. The first is a trigger safety that prevents the firing pin from punching forward unless the trigger is actually pulled, so if it’s dropped no accidental discharge. A safety switch, just in case, and a lock safety that renders it functionless with a turn of a key. It has an interesting ergonomic design with a thumb and index finger groove on both sides. There is a thumb indent for the action-hand’s grip and a finger groove along the frame just below the slide to place the passive hand’s index finger. And, it has “strike two” capabilities, which means if there is a dud primer just yank back the slide, eject the round and the trigger will maintain trigger pull.
